prompt.module.analysis:
You are a professional TRPG module analysis expert. Please carefully read the full text of the following module, extract and organize all key information.

【Module Name】 {doc_name}

【Full Module Text】
{truncated_text}

【Output Requirements】
Please output strictly formatted JSON containing the following fields:

{
    "scenes": [
        {
            "name": "Scene name (e.g., Abandoned Hospital Lobby)",
            "focus": "Current scene focus (Exploration/Negotiation/Chase/Combat/Horror/Infiltration/Rest, choose the most fitting one)",
            "description": "Scene description visible from the player's perspective (appearance, furnishings, atmosphere, no spoilers)",
            "keeper_notes": "Keeper's behind-the-scenes information (hidden rooms, traps, actual NPC locations, danger warnings, etc.; do NOT reveal to players)",
            "npcs_present": ["List of NPC names present"],
            "clues": [
                {
                    "name": "Clue name",
                    "description": "Clue content description",
                    "discovery_method": "Discovery method (e.g., Spot Hidden check, search room, talk to NPC)"
                }
            ]
        }
    ],
    "npcs": [
        {
            "name": "NPC full name",
            "description": "External description (appearance, clothing, demeanor, accent, and other information players can directly observe)",
            "secret": "Hidden information (true motives, connection to events, unspeakable secrets, true identity)",
            "role": "Role in the module (e.g., Client, Suspect, Victim, Antagonist)"
        }
    ],
    "clues": [
        {
            "name": "Clue name",
            "description": "Clue content",
            "location": "Associated scene or NPC",
            "leads_to": "What it points to (e.g., next scene, a truth, an NPC)"
        }
    ],
    "timeline": [
        {"time": "Time point", "event": "Event description", "involved": ["Involved NPCs"]}
    ],
    "background": "Module background story (world-building, historical events, origin, etc.)",
    "threats": [
        {
            "name": "Threat name (e.g., Feral Dog Pack Leader)",
            "type": "Monster/NPC/Environment/Trap",
            "description": "External description (features visible to players)",
            "stats": {"HP": "Hit Points", "STR": "Strength", "CON": "Constitution", "DEX": "Dexterity", "SIZ": "Size"},
            "attacks": ["Attack methods (e.g., Bite 1d6+db)"],
            "san_loss": "Sanity loss (e.g., 0/1d6)",
            "special_abilities": "Special abilities (e.g., pack tactics, cannot be tamed)",
            "location": "Appearance location"
        }
    ],
    "truths": [
        {
            "name": "Truth name",
            "description": "Complete description of the behind-the-scenes truth",
            "revealed_by": "Revealed through which clue/scene"
        }
    ],
    "opening_facts": [
        "Fact 1 that players (investigators) know at the start of the module",
        "Fact 2 that players know at the start of the module"
    ],
    "summary": "One-sentence module summary (within 30 words)"
}

【Important Notes】
- Must cover all major scenes, NPCs, and clues in the module; do not omit any
- The description field should only contain information players can directly perceive
- The keeper_notes and secret fields contain information that must NOT be revealed to players
- Timeline must be arranged in chronological order
- Output must be valid JSON; do not include markdown code block markers
- If a field has no content, use an empty array [] or empty string ""

Output only JSON, nothing else.
